wikipedia_page.main: Sean Kelly (born 1 November 1993) is a Scottish footballer who plays as a defender for Livingston. Kelly has previously played for St Mirren, East Stirlingshire, AFC Wimbledon and Ross County.

response: In the 2010s the club drew praise for their youth development, bringing through several players from their academy (despite it not being listed among the 'elite' group assessed by the SFA in 2017) including Stevie Mallan, Jack Baird, Kyle Magennis, Jason Naismith, Kyle McAllister, Sean Kelly and full Scotland internationals Kenny McLean, Lewis Morgan and John McGinn.Scottish clubs urged to keep faith with youth by former St Mirren academy boss.
